---
import { useTranslations } from '../lib/i18n';
const { lang = 'en' } = Astro.props;

// Model results (hardcoded from stereocilia_bundle_mechanics.py output)
const sweep = [
  { coupling: 0,   abr: 64.0, category: "Moderate-severe" },
  { coupling: 5,   abr: 55.8, category: "Moderate-severe" },
  { coupling: 10,  abr: 52.1, category: "Moderate" },
  { coupling: 20,  abr: 46.7, category: "Moderate" },
  { coupling: 30,  abr: 42.3, category: "Moderate" },
  { coupling: 50,  abr: 34.9, category: "Mild" },
  { coupling: 70,  abr: 28.5, category: "Mild" },
  { coupling: 85,  abr: 24.1, category: "Normal" },
  { coupling: 100, abr: 20.0, category: "Normal" },
];

const therapy = [
  { coupling: 0,  current: 64.0, post: 29.4, gain: 34.6 },
  { coupling: 5,  current: 55.8, post: 28.9, gain: 26.9 },
  { coupling: 10, current: 52.1, post: 28.4, gain: 23.7 },
  { coupling: 20, current: 46.7, post: 27.4, gain: 19.3 },
  { coupling: 30, current: 42.3, post: 26.4, gain: 15.9 },
];

// Misha's estimated range (Sept 2025 audiometry)
const mishaRange = { lo: 0, hi: 30 };

const sweepRows = sweep.map(row => ({
  ...row,
  isMisha: row.coupling >= mishaRange.lo && row.coupling <= mishaRange.hi,
  rowClass: row.coupling >= mishaRange.lo && row.coupling <= mishaRange.hi
    ? 'border-b border-white/[0.03] bg-amber-500/5'
    : 'border-b border-white/[0.03]',
  catClass: row.category === 'Normal'
    ? 'py-2 text-green-400'
    : row.category === 'Mild'
    ? 'py-2 text-yellow-400'
    : 'py-2 text-neutral-400',
}));
---

<section class="px-6 py-16 border-t border-white/5">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400">Stereocilia Bundle Mechanics</h2>
      <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] rounded bg-amber-500/20 text-amber-400 font-semibold">SUPPORTING</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Core claim -->
    <p class="text-neutral-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-2xl">
      OHC function depends on HTC spring coupling maintained by STRC. This model quantifies
      how much coupling remains in DFNB16, what gene therapy adds, and what the actual
      unknown is — it's not OHC survival, it's tectorial membrane remodeling.
    </p>

    <!-- Two-mechanism diagram -->
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-500 mb-4">Why hearing is lost: two mechanisms</h3>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        <div class="bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/5 rounded-lg p-5">
          <div class="text-[10px] font-mono text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">MET channels — 9.5 dB</div>
          <p class="text-xs text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
            HTCs transfer tectorial membrane signal from tallest stereocilia row to shorter rows.
            Without HTCs: only 1 of 3 rows driven. 3× fewer MET channels open = −9.5 dB sensitivity.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/5 rounded-lg p-5">
          <div class="text-[10px] font-mono text-red-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Hopf amplification — 34.5 dB</div>
          <p class="text-xs text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
            OHC active amplification is a Hopf oscillator. Gain scales as f^0.5 where f = HTC coupling.
            Full coupling loss = loss of ~35 dB active gain. This is the dominant mechanism.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-3 bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/5 rounded-lg p-4 flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="text-xs text-neutral-500">Total at f=0:</div>
        <div class="font-mono text-white text-sm">44 dB shift</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-neutral-500">Matches Verpy 2008 Strc−/− data exactly.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Coupling → ABR table -->
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-500 mb-4">HTC coupling → ABR threshold</h3>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-xs">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-neutral-500 font-medium">HTC coupling</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-neutral-500 font-medium">ABR threshold</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 text-neutral-500 font-medium">Category</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {sweepRows.map(row => (
              <tr class={row.rowClass}>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-white">
                  {row.coupling}%
                  {row.isMisha && <span class="ml-2 text-[9px] text-amber-400 font-semibold">← MISHA</span>}
                </td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-neutral-300">{row.abr} dB</td>
                <td class={row.catClass}>{row.category}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-[11px] text-neutral-600 mt-2">
        Misha (Sept 2025 audiometry): right ear 50-65 dB, left ear 40-50 dB → estimated 0-30% residual HTC coupling.
        His VUS allele (c.4976A>C) produces partial stereocilin — he is not a complete knockout.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Gene therapy projection -->
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-500 mb-4">Gene therapy projection (67% OHC transduction)</h3>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-xs">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-neutral-500 font-medium">Current coupling</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-neutral-500 font-medium">Current ABR</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-neutral-500 font-medium">Post-therapy</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 text-neutral-500 font-medium">Improvement</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {therapy.map(row => (
              <tr class="border-b border-white/[0.03]">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-white">{row.coupling}%</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-neutral-400">{row.current} dB</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-green-400">{row.post} dB</td>
                <td class="py-2 font-mono text-white font-semibold">+{row.gain} dB</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-3 bg-green-500/5 border border-green-500/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <div class="text-xs text-green-400 font-semibold mb-1">Post-therapy projection: 26–29 dB</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-neutral-400">Mild hearing loss. Conversational speech without hearing aids.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The open question -->
    <div class="bg-red-500/5 border border-red-500/10 rounded-lg p-5">
      <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-red-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">The unknown: tectorial membrane</div>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-xs text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
        <div>
          <div class="text-neutral-300 font-medium mb-1">What we know</div>
          OHC survival: confirmed even in adult Strc−/− mice (Verpy 2008).
          Stereocilia present. Rootlets anchored. HTC reformation is
          structurally plausible if STRC is delivered.
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-neutral-300 font-medium mb-1">What we don't know</div>
          After 5 years without OHC-TM coupling, has the tectorial membrane
          undergone irreversible structural remodeling? No data exists for
          DFNB16-equivalent at this age in any model. This is the experiment
          that determines whether older patients can be treated.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Citations -->
    <div class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/5">
      <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-500 mb-4">Supporting literature</h3>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="text-[11px] text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          <span class="text-neutral-400 font-medium">Dulon et al. 2019</span> — First direct AFM measurement of HTC spring contribution to OHC bundle stiffness.
          With HTCs: 5.12 pN/nm; without: 2.05 pN/nm. <strong class="text-neutral-400">60% reduction confirmed</strong> with direct measurement.
          IHC stiffness unchanged (HTC contribution is OHC-specific).
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1126/sciadv.aat9934" class="text-neutral-600 hover:text-neutral-400 transition-colors ml-1">Science Advances ↗</a>
        </div>
        <div class="text-[11px] text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          <span class="text-neutral-400 font-medium">Verpy et al. 2011</span> — OHC survival and TM morphology in Strc−/− across ages. At 5 months: basal OHCs damaged, apical preserved.
          TM imprints absent throughout in full KO — structural deficit, not age-related degradation.
          Apical OHCs (low frequency) show <strong class="text-neutral-400">no increased cell loss</strong> vs controls at 5 months.
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/cne.22509" class="text-neutral-600 hover:text-neutral-400 transition-colors ml-1">J Comp Neurol ↗</a>
        </div>
        <div class="text-[11px] text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          <span class="text-neutral-400 font-medium">Tarchini et al. 2021</span> — Dual-AAV STRC therapy at P1. 59% transduction, 50-60 dB rescue in best responders.
          TM attachment crowns reformed even from full KO baseline — TM retains structural capacity to embed stereocilia when STRC is present.
          Adult delivery not tested (explicit limitation). This is the key unanswered question.
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1126/sciadv.abi7629" class="text-neutral-600 hover:text-neutral-400 transition-colors ml-1">Science Advances ↗</a>
        </div>
        <div class="text-[11px] text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          <span class="text-neutral-400 font-medium">Verpy et al. 2008</span> — Strc−/− mouse: ~44 dB threshold shift vs control. Model calibration anchor.
          <span class="text-neutral-600 ml-1">Nature</span>
        </div>
        <div class="text-[11px] text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          <span class="text-neutral-400 font-medium">Camalet et al. 2000</span> — Hopf oscillator model of cochlear amplification. Gain scales as f^0.5 near bifurcation.
          <span class="text-neutral-600 ml-1">PNAS</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Model details -->
    <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-white/5 flex gap-6 text-[11px] text-neutral-600">
      <div>Model: two-component analytical (MET + Hopf)</div>
      <div>Calibration: Verpy 2008 (44 dB at f=0)</div>
      <div>Source: <code class="font-mono">stereocilia_bundle_mechanics.py</code></div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
